<paragraph blockId="12.[117,768,814,1037]" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis box="[163,425,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Callm. &amp; Buerki" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Martelli" box="[457,671,917,941]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="12" pageNumber="335" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="herbacea">
<emphasis box="[457,671,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">Benstonea herbacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in lowland and mountain rainforests (
<quantity box="[496,630,949,973]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="13.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="335" unit="m" value="950.0" valueMax="1300.0" valueMin="600.0">600-1300 m</quantity>
) of northern Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[232,327,981,1005]" name="Malaysia" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and the southern part of 
<collectingCountry box="[588,680,981,1005]" name="Thailand" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="STONE" firstAuthor="STONE" pageId="12" pageNumber="335" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16436" refString="STONE, B. C. (1978). Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores. Fed. Mus. J. 23: 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1978">STONE, 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="335" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[117,769,1053,1333]" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis box="[163,307,1053,1077]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">Observations.</emphasis>
– The collection locality for the type of 
<taxonomicName authority="Martelli" authorityName="Martelli" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="12" pageNumber="335" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">Pandanus herbaceus</emphasis>
Martelli
</taxonomicName>
was cited as “Irang, Penins. Malese (H. Calc.)” (
<bibRefCitation author="MARTELLI" box="[255,498,1117,1141]" firstAuthor="MARTELLI" page="303" pageId="12" pageNumber="335" pagination="298 - 304" refId="ref15762" refString="MARTELLI, U. (1904). Pandani asiatici nuovi. Bull. Soc. Bot. Ital. 1904: 298 - 304." type="journal article" year="1904">MARTELLI, 1904: 303</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="STONE" box="[517,712,1117,1141]" firstAuthor="STONE" page="37" pageId="12" pageNumber="335" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16436" refString="STONE, B. C. (1978). Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores. Fed. Mus. J. 23: 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1978">STONE (1978: 37)</bibRefCitation>
later indicated “ 
<emphasis box="[231,343,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">coll. ignot.</emphasis>
”, but a fragment in Martelli’s herbarium (FI) clearly comes from the type locality cited by Martelli and was collected by H. H. Kunstler 
<emphasis box="[468,638,1213,1237]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">(Kunstler 1397)</emphasis>
,and should be considered as typema terial.Because the 
<typeStatus box="[581,674,1245,1269]" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">holotype</typeStatus>
inCAL was not located by B. C. Stone and appears to have been lost, the collection in FIis here designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[585,686,1309,1333]" pageId="12" pageNumber="335">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
